(478, 'Astros, Aiken camp at odds as signing deadline looms', 'http://mlb.mlb.com/news/article/mlb/astros-brady-aiken-camp-at-odds-as-draft-signing-deadline-looms?ymd=20140716&content_id=84829724&vkey=news_mlb', 'Three days before the July 18 signing deadline for the First-Year Player Draft, it remains unclear whether No. 1 overall pick Brady Aiken will come to terms with the Astros.', 1, 1405515269, 'Wed, 16 Jul 2014 08:54:29 EDT\n	', 0),
(479, 'All-Stars reflect on Jeter''s final Midsummer Classic', 'http://mlb.mlb.com/news/article/mlb/all-stars-reflect-on-derek-jeters-all-star-game-finale?ymd=20140716&content_id=84890806&vkey=news_mlb', 'Derek Jeter''s final All-Star Game went better than anyone could have anticipated. After the game, both teammates and opposing players shared what they thought about playing with or against Jeter in his 14th and final All-Star Game.', 1, 1405493047, 'Wed, 16 Jul 2014 02:44:07 EDT\n	', 0),
(480, 'Twins reflect on success as hosts of All-Star Game', 'http://mlb.mlb.com/news/article/mlb/minnesota-twins-reflect-on-success-as-hosts-of-all-star-game?ymd=20140716&content_id=84890172&vkey=news_mlb', 'A rain shower that delayed Monday''s Gillette Home Run Derby at Target Field couldn''t put a damper on the All-Star festivities in Minnesota, and it did lead to a full rainbow over the ballpark beyond center field as the event began that proved to foreshadow the unforgettable moments that were to come in the Derby and in Tuesday''s 85th All-Star Game.', 1, 1405491527, 'Wed, 16 Jul 2014 02:18:47 EDT\n	', 0),
(481, 'Alexei replaces legend, part of AL''s game-winning rally', 'http://mlb.mlb.com/news/article/mlb/white-sox-shortstop-alexei-ramirez-replaces-derek-jeter-part-of-als-rally?ymd=20140716&content_id=84822490&vkey=news_mlb', 'White Sox shortstop Alexei Ramirez took the reins from Derek Jeter in the fourth inning of Tuesday night''s All-Star Game and then helped the American League stake a claim to home-field advantage in the World Series with a 5-3 victory at Target Field.', 1, 1405490219, 'Wed, 16 Jul 2014 01:56:59 EDT\n	', 0),
(482, 'AL has history on its side going into World Series', 'http://mlb.mlb.com/news/article/mlb/phil-rogers-als-home-field-advantage-makes-league-favorite-for-world-series?ymd=20140716&content_id=84888510&vkey=news_mlb', 'No one knows who is going to wind up with the American League pennant, but the survivor will owe thanks to players all over the league for the home-field advantage it will enjoy.', 1, 1405489467, 'Wed, 16 Jul 2014 01:44:27 EDT\n	', 0),
(483, 'Contrite Wainwright explains Jeter comments', 'http://mlb.mlb.com/news/article/mlb/adam-wainwright-apologizes-for-comments-about-derek-jeter-at-bat?ymd=20140716&content_id=84848282&vkey=news_mlb', 'Adam Wainwright gave up three runs in the first inning of the National League''s 5-3 loss, but his performance on the mound wasn''t what the Cardinals'' ace most regretted about the All-Star Game, it was his poor choice of words after the fact that suggested he took it easy on Derek Jeter during the Yankee legend''s leadoff double.', 1, 1405488904, 'Wed, 16 Jul 2014 01:35:04 EDT\n	', 0),
(484, 'Scherzer earns rare Midsummer Classic win', 'http://mlb.mlb.com/news/article/mlb/tigers-max-scherzer-earns-rare-all-star-game-win?ymd=20140716&content_id=84885138&vkey=news_mlb', 'Considering Max Scherzer kept calling his regular-season wins an overrated stat last year, it probably shouldn''t be a surprise that he wasn''t making a big deal about earning the victory in the 2014 All-Star Game.', 1, 1405487954, 'Wed, 16 Jul 2014 01:19:14 EDT\n	', 0),
(485, 'AL arms rise to occasion, smother NL in crunch time', 'http://mlb.mlb.com/news/article/mlb/phil-rogers-al-arms-rise-to-occasion-smother-nl-in-crunch-time?ymd=20140716&content_id=84884658&vkey=news_mlb', 'From Chris Sale and Max Scherzer to Koji Uehara, Fernando Rodney and hometown hero Glen Perkins, the American League pitchers won one big matchup after another against the National League''s best hitters. In the end, it was enough to allow the AL to hang onto its 5-3 victory.', 1, 1405487833, 'Wed, 16 Jul 2014 01:17:13 EDT\n	', 0),
(486, 'Awed by Jeter, Selig thrilled with MLB''s direction', 'http://mlb.mlb.com/news/article/mlb/awed-by-derek-jeter-commissioner-bud-selig-thrilled-with-mlbs-direction?ymd=20140716&content_id=84883716&vkey=news_mlb', 'After he presented Angels outfielder Mike Trout with the Ted Williams Most Valuable Player Award presented by Chevrolet, after he met retiring Yankees shortstop Derek Jeter outside the dugout for a final embrace, Commissioner Bud Selig took a few moments on Tuesday night to reflect.', 1, 1405487755, 'Wed, 16 Jul 2014 01:15:55 EDT\n	', 0),
(487, 'Perpetual All-Star Jeter never lost modesty', 'http://mlb.mlb.com/news/article/mlb/perpetual-all-star-derek-jeter-maintains-modesty?ymd=20140716&content_id=84881730&vkey=news_mlb', 'There are only a few players who are transcendent figures, even if they might be too modest to admit it. Derek Jeter has been in that category for some time; not only for the quality of his play, not only for the five World Series he has helped the Yankees win, but for the way he has carried himself.', 1, 1405489385, 'Wed, 16 Jul 2014 01:43:05 EDT\n	', 0),
